verbose_text: Various pathophysiological findings have been reported in patients with COM, including biofilm formation in the middle ear, increased levels of the chemokine interleukin (IL) -8 in middle ear effusion, increased levels of the inflammatory cytokines tumor necrosis factor-alpha, IL-6, IL-1beta, and interferon-gamma in the middle ear mucosa, and bony destruction [XREF_BIBR - XREF_BIBR].
